Title : Youth Bandy World Championship
Text : [[File:U23BWC-2011-rus-fin.jpg|thumb|Russia vs. Finland at the World Championship Y23 in 2011]]
'''Bandy World Championship for youth teams''' are held in a number of age classes for boys and young men and in one age class for girls playing [[bandy]]. The tournaments are governed by the [[Federation of International Bandy]].<ref name=tournaments>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldbandy.com/tournaments.asp?pageID=0 |title=Tournaments |publisher=Federation of International Bandy |accessdate=30 April 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091028045110/http://www.geocities.com/Colosseum/Track/2049/Kalenderbiteri/VMres.html |archivedate=October 28, 2009 }}</ref>

The following tournaments are held regularly:<ref name=tournaments/>
*World Championship G17, for girls' teams up to age 17
*World Championship Y15, for boys' teams up to age 15
*World Championship Y17, for boys' teams up to age 17
*World Championship Y19, for young men's teams up to age 19
*World Championship Y23, for young men's teams up to age 23

G17 is sometimes written as F17 and the Y designations may also be written with a U.

==G17==
{{Main|Bandy World Championship G-17}}
The first World Championship G17 was held in 2009 and it has since been held every other year.<ref name=sbff17>{{cite web|url=http://iof1.idrottonline.se/SvenskaBandyforbundet/Landslag/F17-landslaget/Historikochstatistik/|title=F17-landslaget: Historik och statistik|publisher=[[Swedish Bandy Association]]|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref>

===Champions===
* 2009 {{flagicon|Russia}} Russia<ref name=bandysidan>{{cite web|url=http://www.bandysidan.nu/tavlinginfo.php?sprak=eng&land=3|title=Evenemang|publisher=Bandysidan|accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref>
* 2011 {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden<ref name=sbff17/>
* 2013 {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldbandy.com/wcsg17/news.asp?newsid=501&t=Rosabollen_summerar_m%E4sterskapet|title=Rosa bollen summerar mästerskapet|publisher=[[Federation of International Bandy]]|language=Swedish|date=18 February 2013|accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref>
* 2015 {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden<ref>[http://www.usabandy.com/f17worldchampionships USA Bandy: F17 World Championships], retrieved 12 March 2015</ref>
* 2017 {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden
* 2019 {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden

==Y15==
The first World Championship Y16 was held in 1994. Starting with 2002, it has been for Y15 teams since.<ref name=sbfp15>{{cite web|url=http://iof1.idrottonline.se/SvenskaBandyforbundet/Landslag/P15-landslaget/Historikochstatistik/|title=P15-landslaget: Historik och statistik|publisher=[[Swedish Bandy Association]]|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref>

